# Book: 2Corinthians

# Section: Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus
# 2Corinthians 01:01
Paul,
  an apostle of Christ Jesus
    through the will of God,
and Timothy our brother.

# Section: To the assembly of God which is at Corinth
To the assembly of God which is at Corinth,
with all the saints who are in the whole of Achaia:

# Section: Grace to you and peace
# 2Corinthians 01:02
Grace to you and peace
  from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.

# Section: Blessed be the God and Father
# 2Corinthians 01:03
STARTHERE

Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,
the Father of mercies and God of all comfort,
# 2Corinthians 01:04
who comforts us in all our affliction,
that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction,
through the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.

# 2Corinthians 01:05
For as the sufferings of Christ abound to us,
even so our comfort also abounds through Christ.

# 2Corinthians 01:06
But if we are afflicted,
it is for your comfort and salvation.

If we are comforted,
it is for your comfort,
which produces in you the patient enduring
of the same sufferings which we also suffer.

# 2Corinthians 01:07
Our hope for you is steadfast,
knowing that,
since you are partakers of the sufferings,
so you are also of the comfort.

# 2Corinthians 01:08
For we don’t desire to have you uninformed,
brothers,
concerning our affliction which happened to us in Asia:
that we were weighed down exceedingly,
beyond our power,
so much that we despaired even of life.

# 2Corinthians 01:09
Yes,
we ourselves have had the sentence of death within ourselves,
that we should not trust in ourselves,
but in God who raises the dead,

# 2Corinthians 01:10
